From 3e052889b1719cb16db73a7784be08582d107f6b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Khiem Nguyen <khiem.nguyen.xt@renesas.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Feb 2021 20:48:55 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 04/15] uio: Fix the logic of setting reset to UIO devices

Current flow does not call reset_control_assert()
but reset_control_reset() which lead to incorrect internal state
in next getting reset calls.
Moreover, it's still valid to trigger a reset in case the reset
function is called with other values than 0/1.

This patch fixes the logic.

Signed-off-by: Khiem Nguyen <khiem.nguyen.xt@renesas.com>
---
 drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
index 14e4dafdfefe..1397f48af512 100644
--- a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
+++ b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
@@ -262,11 +262,11 @@ static void priv_set_rst(struct uio_info *info, int value)
 			reset_control_deassert(priv->rst);
 		break;
 	case 1:
-		reset_control_reset(priv->rst);
+		reset_control_assert(priv->rst);
 		break;
 	default:
 		if (status == 0)
-			reset_control_assert(priv->rst);
+			reset_control_reset(priv->rst);
 		break;
 	}
 
